Great question! In Rust, you’d use the `enumerate` method on an iterator to get both the index and value. Here’s how you could do it:

```rust
let fruits = vec!['apple', 'banana', 'cherry'];
for (i, fruit) in fruits.iter().enumerate() {
    println!("{}: {}"," i, fruit);
}
```
This will print each fruit with its position. The `enumerate` method wraps an iterator and yields tuples of `(index, value)`."
